/-- **Vanishing on scalar‚Ä¢V inputs**:
`bch_septic_term ùïÇ (Œ± ‚Ä¢ V) (Œ≤ ‚Ä¢ V) = 0` for any `Œ±, Œ≤ : ùïÇ` and `V : ùî∏`.

Source: `log(exp(Œ±V)¬∑exp(Œ≤V)) = (Œ±+Œ≤)V` (V commutes with itself), so all
deg-7 Taylor content must vanish identically as a polynomial in (Œ±, Œ≤).

Proof template mirrors `symmetric_bch_septic_poly_apply_smul_smul`:
1. Collapse each 7-fold product `(Œ±V)^k¬∑(Œ≤V)^(7‚àík)` to `(Œ±^k¬∑Œ≤^(7‚àík)) ‚Ä¢ V‚Å∑`.
2. Combine the 126 word coefficients into a single polynomial in (Œ±, Œ≤)
   times `V‚Å∑`.
3. The polynomial-in-(Œ±, Œ≤) identity (each `(k, 7‚àík)` partial sum is 0)
   is closed by `ring`. -/
theorem bch_septic_term_apply_smul_smul (V : ùî∏) (Œ± Œ≤ : ùïÇ) :
    bch_septic_term ùïÇ (Œ± ‚Ä¢ V) (Œ≤ ‚Ä¢ V) = 0 := by
  unfold bch_septic_term
  -- Step 1: collapse each 7-fold product to (scalar) ‚Ä¢ V‚Å∑; combine outer scalars.
  simp only [bch_septic_term_seven_fold_smul_mul_eq, smul_smul, ‚Üê add_smul]
  -- Step 2: goal is now `(big_polynomial in Œ±, Œ≤) ‚Ä¢ V‚Å∑ = 0`.
  conv_rhs => rw [show (0 : ùî∏) = (0 : ùïÇ) ‚Ä¢ (V * V * V * V * V * V * V) from
    (zero_smul _ _).symm]
