set_option maxHeartbeats 800000 in
/-- **Lipschitz bound for `bch_septic_term`**: `‚ÄñZ‚Çá(z, y) ‚àí Z‚Çá(x, y)‚Äñ ‚â§ 7¬∑M‚Å∂¬∑‚Äñz‚àíx‚Äñ`
where `M = ‚Äñz‚Äñ+‚Äñx‚Äñ+‚Äñy‚Äñ`.

Analog of `norm_bch_sextic_term_diff_le` at one degree higher; with
`z = (a'+b) + W` and `‚ÄñW‚Äñ = O(s¬≤)`, gives an O(s‚Å∏¬∑‚ÄñW‚Äñ) bound on
`‚ÄñC‚Çá(z, y) ‚àí C‚Çá(a'+b, y)‚Äñ`. Foundation for stepping stone 1
(`symmetric_bch_septic_sub_poly_axiom` discharge).

The proof uses a uniform per-i bound `(216/30240) ¬∑ 7 ¬∑ M‚Å∂ ¬∑ ‚Äñz‚àíx‚Äñ`,
giving `Œ£ ‚â§ 126¬∑216¬∑7/30240 = 190512/30240 = 63/10 ‚â§ 7`. -/
theorem norm_bch_septic_term_diff_le (z x y : ùî∏) :
    ‚Äñbch_septic_term ùïÇ z y - bch_septic_term ùïÇ x y‚Äñ ‚â§
      7 * (‚Äñz‚Äñ + ‚Äñx‚Äñ + ‚Äñy‚Äñ) ^ 6 * ‚Äñz - x‚Äñ := by
  set M := ‚Äñz‚Äñ + ‚Äñx‚Äñ + ‚Äñy‚Äñ with hM_def
  have hM_nn : 0 ‚â§ M := by positivity
  have hz_le : ‚Äñz‚Äñ ‚â§ M := by
    show ‚Äñz‚Äñ ‚â§ ‚Äñz‚Äñ + ‚Äñx‚Äñ + ‚Äñy‚Äñ; linarith [norm_nonneg x, norm_nonneg y]
  have hx_le : ‚Äñx‚Äñ ‚â§ M := by
    show ‚Äñx‚Äñ ‚â§ ‚Äñz‚Äñ + ‚Äñx‚Äñ + ‚Äñy‚Äñ; linarith [norm_nonneg z, norm_nonneg y]
  have hy_le : ‚Äñy‚Äñ ‚â§ M := by
    show ‚Äñy‚Äñ ‚â§ ‚Äñz‚Äñ + ‚Äñx‚Äñ + ‚Äñy‚Äñ; linarith [norm_nonneg z, norm_nonneg x]
  have hM6_nn : 0 ‚â§ M^6 := pow_nonneg hM_nn 6
  have hzx_nn : 0 ‚â§ ‚Äñz - x‚Äñ := norm_nonneg _
  rw [bch_septic_term_eq_sum, bch_septic_term_eq_sum, ‚Üê Finset.sum_sub_distrib]
  calc ‚Äñ‚àë i : Fin 126, (bchSepticTerm (ùïÇ := ùïÇ) z y i - bchSepticTerm (ùïÇ := ùïÇ) x y i)‚Äñ
      ‚â§ ‚àë i : Fin 126, ‚ÄñbchSepticTerm (ùïÇ := ùïÇ) z y i - bchSepticTerm (ùïÇ := ùïÇ) x y i‚Äñ := norm_sum_le _ _
    _ ‚â§ ‚àë _i : Fin 126, (216 / 30240 : ‚Ñù) * 7 * M^6 * ‚Äñz - x‚Äñ :=
        Finset.sum_le_sum (fun i _ => bchSepticTerm_diff_norm_le (ùïÇ := ùïÇ) z x y M hz_le hx_le hy_le hM_nn i)
    _ = 126 * ((216 / 30240 : ‚Ñù) * 7 * M^6 * ‚Äñz - x‚Äñ) := by
        rw [Finset.sum_const, Finset.card_univ, Fintype.card_fin]; ring
    _ ‚â§ 7 * M^6 * ‚Äñz - x‚Äñ := by nlinarith [hM6_nn, hzx_nn]

/-! ### `bch_octic_term` ‚Äî the œÑ‚Å∏ coefficient of `bch(a, b)`

Explicit 124-term polynomial in {a, b}, derived via the CAS pipeline at
`scripts/compute_bch_octic_term.py`. Common denominator 120960; integer
numerators in {¬±2, ¬±12, ¬±23, ¬±30, ¬±40, ¬±54, ¬±72, ¬±96, ¬±432}.
Sum of |numerators|/120960 = 5970/120960 = 199/4032 ‚âà 0.0494.

This is the next term in the BCH expansion after `bch_septic_term`:
`bch(a, b) = a + b + ¬Ω[a,b] + Z‚ÇÉ + Z‚ÇÑ + Z‚ÇÖ + Z‚ÇÜ + Z‚Çá + Z‚Çà + O(¬∑^9)`.

Used in the future nonic identity (stepping stone 1) for canceling deg-8
contributions to `sym_bch_cubic - sym_E‚ÇÉ - sym_E‚ÇÖ - sym_E‚Çá` (the deg-9
analog of the discharged `symmetric_bch_quintic_sub_poly_axiom`). -/

/-- **œÑ‚Å∏ coefficient of `bch(a, b)`** ‚Äî explicit 124-term polynomial in
{a, b}. The 124 non-zero 8-letter words (out of 256 = 2‚Å∏ possible) come
from the free Lie algebra basis at degree 8. Coefficients are rational
with LCM 120960. -/
