/-- **Fourth-order BCH**: `bch(a,b) = (a+b) + ¬Ω[a,b] + bch_cubic_term(a,b) + O(s‚Å¥)`.

This extends H1 by identifying the cubic coefficient `(1/12)([a,[a,b]]+[b,[b,a]])`.
The proof extracts the quartic log remainder `logOnePlus(y)-y+¬Ωy¬≤-‚Öìy¬≥` and the
degree-3 algebraic terms, showing they combine to `bch_cubic_term`. -/
theorem norm_bch_quartic_remainder_le (a b : ùî∏) (hab : ‚Äña‚Äñ + ‚Äñb‚Äñ < Real.log 2) :
    ‚Äñbch (ùïÇ := ùïÇ) a b - (a + b) - (2 : ùïÇ)‚Åª¬π ‚Ä¢ (a * b - b * a) -
      bch_cubic_term ùïÇ a b‚Äñ ‚â§
      200 * (‚Äña‚Äñ + ‚Äñb‚Äñ) ^ 4 / (2 - Real.exp (‚Äña‚Äñ + ‚Äñb‚Äñ)) := by
  -- SETUP: same as H1
